headlines.description: — Jalen Hurts shrugged on a TD celebration and did his best to be like Mike.
headlines.shortLinkText: Defending champion Eagles edge Cowboys 24-20 in wild, lightning-delayed NFL season opener

events.name: Kansas City Chiefs at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: Justin Herbert finished off the Los Angeles Chargers' season-opening victory in style, sliding for a first down that effectively ended the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herbert outduels Mahomes to help the Chargers beat the Chiefs 27-21 in Brazil

events.name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Atlanta Falcons

headlines.description: — Another visit to Mercedes-Benz Stadium produced more lasting memories for Emeka Egbuka.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buccaneers ride 2 TD catches by rookie Egbuka to dramatic 23-20 win over Penix, Falcons

headlines.description: — DJ Turner and the Bengals defense heard the narrative throughout the offseason that they were mainly the reason why Cincinnati missed the playoffs last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bengals defense leads the way to 17-16 win over the Browns in opener

headlines.description: — Indianapolis Colts quarterback Daniel Jones delivered the perfect start.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daniel Jones shines as Colts snap 11-game opening-day winless streak, beating Dolphins 33-8

events.name: Las Vegas Raiders at New England Patriots

headlines.description: — With his team leading by 10 points and facing a long third down late in the fourth, Las Vegas Raiders quarterback Geno Smith was calm.
headlines.shortLinkText: Geno Smith passes for 362 yards and a TD in Raiders debut as Vegas thwarts Patriots 20-13

events.name: Arizona Cardinals at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: — Kyler Murray felt ill when he woke up Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray throws 2 TD passes to help the Cardinals hold on 20-13 in Saints coach Moore's debut

events.name: Pittsburgh Steelers at New York Jets

headlines.description: — Aaron Rodgers turned back the clock with a vintage performance in his Steelers debut that featured big throws, no turnovers and a late victory over...
headlines.shortLinkText: Aaron Rodgers throws 4 TD passes in his Steelers debut, leads 34-32 comeback win over Jets

events.name: New York Giants at Washington Commanders

headlines.description: — When Washington lost in the NFC title game in January, the Commanders were so overmatched against Philadelphia's tush push that officials threatened to...
headlines.shortLinkText: Samuel scores in Washington debut, and the Commanders stifle the Giants in a 21-6 win

headlines.description: — New Jaguars coach Liam Coen tried to stay out of the limelight in the postgame locker room. Team owner Shad Khan wouldn't let him.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lawrence and Etienne deliver as Jaguars open new regime with a 26-10 victory over the Panthers

headlines.description: — Denver's ferocious defense has no bigger fan than Bo Nix.
headlines.shortLinkText: Broncos spoil Cam Ward's debut with a 20-12 win over the Titans

headlines.description: — When Brock Purdy commanded the huddle ahead of the San Francisco 49ers’ final drive, he provided a clear message to third-string tight end Jake Tonges and the rest of the offense.
headlines.shortLinkText: Third-stringer Jake Tonges' late TD catch gives the 49ers a 17-13 win over the Seahawks

events.name: Detroit Lions at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: — Micah Parsons' arrival in Green Bay helped the Packers put their recent NFC North struggles behind them.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Love starts fast and Parsons gets a sack in his Green Bay debut as Packers defeat Lions 27-13

events.name: Houston Texans at Los Angeles Rams

headlines.shortLinkText: Stafford tops 60,000 yards passing, defense stands strong as Rams hold off Texans 14-9

headlines.description: — Josh Allen had a message to the few thousands fans — and perhaps the entire NFL, for that matter — who left the stadium early to beat the traffic on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Josh Allen rallies Bills for 16 points in last 4 minutes to stun Ravens 41-40 in prime-time thriller

headlines.description: — J.J. McCarthy’s long-awaited debut for the Minnesota Vikings was looking more like a nightmare.
